body:
Given the following code: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=b413ed034f662797ddfe5dfc6772a277

```rust
struct Scanner<'a> {
    input: &'a str
}

impl<'a> Scanner<'a> {
    pub fn scan(&self) -> Token {
        Token {
            input: self.input
        }
    }
    
}

struct Token<'a> {
    input: &'a str

}

fn scan(input: &str) -> Token {
    Scanner { input }.scan()
}
```

The current output is:

```
error[E0515]: cannot return reference to temporary value
  --> src/lib.rs:20:5
   |
20 |     Scanner { input }.scan()
   |     -----------------^^^^^^^
   |     |
   |     returns a reference to data owned by the current function
   |     temporary value created here

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0515`.
error: could not compile `playground` due to previous error
```

<!-- The following is not always necessary. -->
Ideally the output should look like:

```
    pub fn scan(&self) -> Token {
                              ^ try adding <'a>: `Token<'a>`
```
but more pretty
